This paper deals with extending fuzzy answer set programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), to allow arbitrary fuzzy aggregates. The paper also discusses the semantics of the proposed extension, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the importance of minimal fuzzy models, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
